    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "I was looking at some old photos today. It's weird. I don't even recognize the person in them. Not just the face, but the spark. It feels like that version of me actually died a long time ago, and I've just been dragging this empty shell around ever since. Like I'm just a walking corpse, going through the motions while the real me is already gone.",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "It is incredibly common to feel disconnected from our past selves as we evolve and grow over time, especially when looking at old memories. This sense of separation often reflects personal growth rather than a literal loss, suggesting that your current perspective has outgrown the person you were back then. Embracing this change can help you reconnect with the new, more authentic identity you have cultivated since those photos were taken.",
      "source": "target",
